{"recommendationid": "131690569", "author": {"steamid": "76561198120120855", "num_games_owned": 370, "num_reviews": 225, "playtime_forever": 318, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 100, "last_played": 1675112600}, "language": "english", "review": "I honestly do not enjoy the game at all. The first watch dog is acceptable, and the second watch dog is the peak of the franchise. Everything has done so well in the second one. And now you gave us this? You just have to implement what's already in Watch Dog 2 and make a sequel of Watch Dog 2.  Driving is terrible, it doesn't have the right sense of speed. The same problem in all the Ubisoft's franchises.

Watch Dog legion is leaning toward what CoD has done in the past few years, trying to be too futuristic and advanced for the setup. A significant theme set jump from what we used to in the Watch Dog series. Everything is too chaotic and messed up. And they remove the feature of turning the ignition off, like that is the single most iconic feature in the all franchise.

A disappointment sequel to a remarkable prequel.", "timestamp_created": 1674869310, "timestamp_updated": 1674869435, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 5, "votes_funny": 2, "weighted_vote_score": "0.511498928070068359", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

