If you've never played Watch Dogs, I highly recommend Watch Dogs 2 instead of whatever this was trying to be.", "timestamp_created": 1674931103, "timestamp_updated": 1674931103, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 6, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.536156654357910156", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "131779828", "author": {"steamid": "76561198009600535", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 13, "playtime_forever": 2463, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 406, "last_played": 1685013226}, "language": "english", "review": "This game is a lot of fun.  Plenty of people are hating on it cos of Ubisoft's stance on Steam and that seems like an unfair way to rate a game.  

On its merits, this game runs smoothly for the most part but there are occasional framerate drops in very heavily populated areas when there's a lot going on (using an RTX 3070 here) at full graphics in 1080p.  The gameplay is varied enough to keep you interested, there are plenty of fun and engaging characters, and the options for customisation and car and weapon variation make for some stunning visuals and interesting scenes.  Combat is suitably tough (I'd recommend playing with perma-death on, though) and the stealth is well rounded.  Each area and mission has numerous ways to solve it and the addition of numerous factions and the ability to recruit from within them makes for exciting, tense moments.

For my money, especially at 80% off, this is a solid 8/10.", "timestamp_created": 1674971865, "timestamp_updated": 1674971865, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 8, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.538585484027862549", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "131839655", "author": {"steamid": "76561198000007846", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 24, "playtime_forever": 244, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 237, "last_played": 1675037791}, "language": "english", "review": "I'm really surprised about this game, it's much worse than Watch dogs 2. Fundamentally, the concept of playing as different random people is an awful idea. I respect that they tried something different here, but it doesn't add to the playing experience. You don't have any connection to the characters you play. If the gaming industry has learned anything from RPGs. it's that gamers like creating a character that they identify with, either as a reflection of themselves, or something completely different that is interesting to them. In this case, we are forced to play as random characters, most of which look like edgy teenagers. 

Another thing that I think was better in other games was the world itself. This weird paramilitary police state version of London is awful. Its not remotely relatable or realistic, and it's incredibly depressing. It doesn't feel like the world has any real life to it, its just a series of cartoon characters. All the characters are doing a weird post apocalyptic dress up. You don't have cars, you can only steal them from the street, while claiming to be "making london a better place". Any character customization is done through a vending machine, there doesn't seem to be shops anymore that you can go in to interact with people. Everything just feels very fake ... 

I really liked the first two games, I played them a lot. So I hope that they make a new one, and I hope it's something that feels more real and less of a depressing cartoon.", "timestamp_created": 1675037448, "timestamp_updated": 1675037448, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 2, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.508908689022064209", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "131841671", "author": {"steamid": "76561198050733614", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 5, "playtime_forever": 2830, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 387, "last_played": 1679360878}, "language": "english", "review": "Go Play Watch Dogs 2. This game is not worth it. The setting of the game is depressing as it's always dreary.

The Story. DedSec is framed, and you have to recruit people to join, who you can then use on missions. There's no attachment to the characters you play as since they're all generic.

The 'multiplayer'. You have two gamemodes, Playlist and Paper Trail, as well as two pvp modes. They're both dull and get repetitive very, very quickly. There's no co-op campaign, which is why I'm currently asking for a refund.", "timestamp_created": 1675040541, "timestamp_updated": 1675040541, "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 14, "votes_funny": 2, "weighted_vote_score": "0.566541969776153564", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

{"recommendationid": "131851104", "author": {"steamid": "76561198008573498", "num_games_owned": 606, "num_reviews": 66, "playtime_forever": 4308, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 691, "last_played": 1676093685}, "language": "english", "review": "Enjoying this title quite a bit. It's not a masterpiece but at 80% off it is definitely worth the price. I haven't played too far through the storyline at the moment as I'm having a lot of fun completing recruit missions. Which is just as well as I have permadeath enabled and keep losing agents.

Ubisoft did a good job of creating London. The visuals look really good though it's no doubt a lot dimmer and darker than the game from memory. Performance wise, it works very well. No stutters or frame drops. Only had a couple of issues 12hrs in which were one offs. Issue with connecting to Ubisoft which eventually resolved itself and the game bugged out when it should have initiated a cut scene with a potential recruit. The cutscene didn't eventuate and my character was stuck on the spot with no way to re initiate the quest or go elsewhere. Had to cntr/alt/delete to get out and fire up the game again. 

As mentioned, I'm enjoying the game. Wouldn't pay full price but did purchase the "Ultimate Edition" for $35AUD. Don't be put off by the trolls feeding off of each other in the review section.", "timestamp_created": 1675055382, "timestamp_updated": 1675055382, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 4, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": "0.548872172832489014", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

