{"recommendationid": "132080705", "author": {"steamid": "76561198341343474", "num_games_owned": 0, "num_reviews": 146, "playtime_forever": 2008, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 2008, "last_played": 1675365678}, "language": "english", "review": "This game is fun, it's a great GTA clone, and it has the unique twist of Watch Dogs (I personally love the gameplay). The stealth element is kinda frustrating as it's a painstakingly long process to infiltrate, and you get detected in absolutely ridiculous ways. So I played as GTA, shooting everyone. It's filled with bugs but none too severe to affect gameplay. The story is kinda meh, average cookie cutter fight against evil villains story and with an obvious twist. Some of the subplots are really interesting though, mainly the spy story and the Skye Larsen story.

I only bothered with the Bagley side missions because he's the only character I liked and whose story I was invested in. The play as anyone mechanic is good, but the consequence is not having any strong characters as protagonists.

All in all a decent experience and well worth the price if on sale. It's certainly not worth full price unless you're a die hard watch dogs fan and/or love GTA clones.. This game is a "play once, forget about it" game.", "timestamp_created": 1675366103, "timestamp_updated": 1675366103, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 1, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

