{"recommendationid": "132354804", "author": {"steamid": "76561197971537739", "num_games_owned": 186, "num_reviews": 95, "playtime_forever": 12502, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 5599, "last_played": 1757325262}, "language": "english", "review": "There are good and bad parts of this game but unfortunately the bads overpower the goods. I liked Watch Dogs 1 and 2, but Legions sadly doesn’t have a solid singleplayer story due to its novel structure. If you are into character collection then I think you should give it a go, but not having a “main protagonist” makes it hard to care about the individuals in an organization that fights for personal freedom.

I think the character collection structure could work for a semi-persistent online format. In fact, the gun fight combat of this game seems to be optimized for multiplayer cooperation rather than singleplayer, and causes problems with being alone in the story mode, defending a hacking area while enemies have endless spawns and will coordinate to flank you from all sides.

